Under the above optimum conditions, we determined the ECL intensities of chlorpyrifos at different concentrations (Fig.6
                        ). As the concentration of chlorpyrifos increased, the ECL intensity increased, because the Ag/CQDs-aptamer was separated from the electrode surface as the double strands were untwisted. The ECL intensity was positively correlated with the logarithm of chlorpyrifos concentration in 1.0 fM ∼ 10 nM. The linear equation was I = 18,403 + 893lgc with the related coefficient of 0.994 and the LOD of 0.35 fM (S/N = 3). This aptasensor had excellent analytical performance compared with other analytical methods (Table 1
                        ).
